<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Development Update - Game Balance</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=595368" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>Yesterday on <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/"target=blank>EQ Live</a> the EverQuest development team released some information regarding class balancing issues, and changes you can expect to see in the upcoming patch (<a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/support/scheduled_downtime.jsp"target=blank>Wednesday, October 16th</a>). <br><br>

Changes are being made to:<br>
<blockquote><li>Wizard Alternate Advancement - specifically Manaburn
<li>The use of Rods of Mystical Transvergence
<li>Cleric's Complete Healing hitpoints cap
<li>Monk defense and Armor Class</blockquote>

The scale of changes being made is large, and talk has already been growing in our <a href="http://www.everlore.com/MB_SHOW.asp?FID=76&FN=MainHall&SID=7&SN=Everlore&TID=1726368&TN=Best+Patch%2E+Ever%2E&CAT=General&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&PL=3"target=blank>Main Hall</a>. Opinions seem to be mixed; What some are calling crucial class-balancing changes, others are calling an unnecessary nerf. Click <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/articles.jsp?id=52118"target=blank>here</a> to read the full article submitted by the EQ Development Team, and then come back to let us know what <b>you</b> think.</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=595368">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
