				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hehe..sounds like a problem for the higher levels.<BR>
I do want to say a few things though.<BR>
I been messing around with this game for almost as long as it has been out,it`s a very fun game, and has made alot of my limited free time pass by like a flowing stream..I do say limited free time..cos I`m just a &quot;casual&quot; player..you know..one of those folks that usually just has time to play a bit on weekends.<BR>
The one thing I always hated about EQ, is &quot;The Group or Die&quot; concept this game, pretty much has always had.<BR>
Now I think it is pretty fekkin ridiculos, to need to have about 30 or more pc`s to kill a npc.<BR>
Do you know how difficult it is to get a large number of ego`s like that together, and take down a mob, maybe to just benifit one person?<BR>
As a casual player, who doesn`t have the time to play every day..it`s darn near impossible...Hmmm..maybe thats why I have found that the higher of level I get..the less fun the game becomes.<BR>
So I just usually mess around in the lower levels. The change I would like to see the most in this game..is to loosen up on the &quot;group or die concept&quot; and allow for people to be able to play the game BY THEMSELVES if they wish to do so...oh..I think the term is SOLOING..lol.<BR>
Don`t get me wrong..I`m not against grouping..I just think we ..as players should be given the choice to solo, and not have to get in a group to get any experince or loot.<BR>
That would be a great thing for Verant to put in EQ2..I would definatly go to that, if they did...
