	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   What this whole debate is really about is change: who can handle it. adapt to it, and who cannot.  Some classes had their favorite toys taken away and replaced with inferior models.  Waah, boo-hoo.  Learn to live with it.  I started my main into Jewelcraft because I fell in love with all of the plat that crafters were making via selling in FayMart.  Then, when I finally got my skill up to where I could be one of the moneymakers, the whole aspect of the game changed and the bazaar was brought in.  Now pieces that sold more more than 1000 plat go for somwhere around 200 or less.  Free enterprise at work for your tax dollars.<BR>
   Was I upset?  Torqued off?  You bet your butt I was!  I felt burned and abused because I had spent thousands of plat learning a now profitless skill.  I raged a while and then I saw what was happening around me.  Previously useful class-skills (Teleporting, KEI casting, ressurrections, etc.) were suddenly the hot commodities.  I've seen a 60th level enchanter walk to the bank with over 5,000 plat in his pocket after a long day at Nexus.  I, myself, have taken in over 2,000 just on teleporting if I'm having an &quot;I'm incredibly tired of fighting&quot; days.<BR>
   So, to the wizards who lost their money-making Manaburn, and the mages as well, I say Get Over It!  Learn to adapt and move on or get a new character.  If you can't adapt, then perhaps you chose the wrong character to play.  And as for Mages now being useless in a party, I say that I'd rather have the mage's pet taking hits than having the mob hitting me while I'm trying to cast spells.<BR>
   Jeez.  Quit whining and start playing.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
